Gawker as well.

24:21.060 --> 24:23.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now, nothing
that Peter
Thiel is doing is illegal. There
are not any

24:23.696 --> 24:28.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
laws on the books that say you
can't fund
or aid someone else's legal
pursuit, right?

24:28.867 --> 24:33.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's a kind of a bigger
question here
of this is a billionaire using a
tremendous

24:33.939 --> 24:40.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
amount of influence. He's an
ardent libertarian
who does speak up on behalf of
free speech,

24:40.946 --> 24:46.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but here he is crushing an
institution that
said something that he was,
well, ticked off

24:46.552 --> 24:48.253 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
about.

24:48.287 --> 24:51.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JASON TANZ: Yes, I mean, the
tricky thing
about this is, Thiel feels
wronged, but he

24:51.957 --> 24:57.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is not suing Gawker based on the
statement
that he feels wronged him. He's
not suing

24:57.196 --> 24:59.064 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
them for outing him.

24:59.098 --> 25:04.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's suing them for Hogan. And
based on his
actions and based on Hogan's
actions, it doesn't

25:04.803 --> 25:08.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
